			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2015-10-08T17:25:00-07:00" itemprop="datePublished"><a href="https://blog.sucuri.net/2015/10/brute-force-amplification-attacks-against-wordpress-xmlrpc.html#comment-6780">October 8, 2015</a></time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>I have been recommending disabling XMLRPC to all our clients for the past 2 years since we got a major attack which was causing php spikes every 10 minutes 24/7, and other stuff not good. Most attacks came from Ukraine, so blocking that helped, too (still good to check logs to see WHO is actually attacking you!). 🙂</p>
		</div>

		
		
	</article>
