		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Might be interesting: I dug through my own logfiles, and it occurred to me that most POST requests are sent to my non-SSL URL, which is 301 redirected to HTTPS (and thus losing it&#8217;s POST payload). I have some 876 kB of &#8220;POST /xmlrpc.php&#8221; log lines this month alone</p>
		</div>

		
		
	</article>
