	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-7486">
	<article >

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/21bf480a84fcc2051cdd6c8bb079248c?s=48&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/21bf480a84fcc2051cdd6c8bb079248c?s=96&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' loading='lazy'/><span itemprop="name">Michael DeMutis</span> 			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-04-14T03:36:00-07:00" itemprop="datePublished"><a href="https://blog.sucuri.net/2015/10/brute-force-amplification-attacks-against-wordpress-xmlrpc.html#comment-7486">April 14, 2016</a></time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>To block it on a later version of Apache use:<br />
<code></p>
<p>Require all denied<br />
ErrorDocument 403 http://127.0.0.1/</p>
<p></code></p>
<p>in your Virtualhost configurations.  The &#8220;Order by&#8221; method is a way old version and won&#8217;t work on modern Apache 2.4.x installations.</p>
<p><b>Note: This disqus editor adds =&#8221;&#8221; to the end of the files directive, that should not be there.</b></p>
		</div>

		
		
	</article>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->

